Package sprouts.impl

Class PropertyChangeListeners<T>

java.lang.Object
sprouts.impl.PropertyChangeListeners<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of the property that this listener listens to.
public final class PropertyChangeListeners<T> extends Object
This class is technically an internal class and should not be used directly. If you use this class directly, most likely, you are at risk of your code breaking in future releases of Sprouts.

    • PropertyChangeListeners

      public PropertyChangeListeners(PropertyChangeListeners<T> other)

      Parameters:

  • Method Details

    • onChange

      public void onChange(Channel channel, Action<ValDelegate<T>> action)
      Adds a change listener for the given channel. This method is used to register a listener that will be notified when the property changes.
      Parameters:
      channel - The channel on which the change listener will be registered.
      action - The action to be performed when the property changes.

    • updateState

      public void updateState(@Nullable Channel channel, Function<sprouts.impl.ChangeListeners<ValDelegate<T>>,sprouts.impl.ChangeListeners<ValDelegate<T>>> updater)

    • onChange

      public void onChange(Observer observer)
      Adds a plain observer (has no delegate) as a change listener for the default channel, which is defined by SproutsFactory.defaultObservableChannel(). The listener will be notified when the property changes, or when it is triggered explicitly through (Val.fireChange(Channel)).
      Parameters:
      observer - The observer to be registered as a change listener.

    • unsubscribe

      public void unsubscribe(Subscriber subscriber)
      Unsubscribes a Subscriber from the change listeners. This method is used to remove a listener that was previously registered. Note that the Subscriber is a marker interface as well as common super type for all listeners that are registered to the change listeners.
      Parameters:
      subscriber - The subscriber to be removed from the change listeners.

    • unsubscribeAll

      public void unsubscribeAll()
      Unsubscribes all change listeners from this PropertyChangeListeners. This method is used to remove all listeners that were previously registered. Note that this will remove all listeners, regardless of the channel they were registered on.

    • fireChange

      public void fireChange(Val<T> owner, Channel channel, @Nullable T newValue, @Nullable T oldValue)
      Fires a change event for the given property and channel. This method is used to notify all listeners that a change has occurred. This is not currently used internally, but may be useful for deeply integrated libraries built on top of sprouts.
      Parameters:
      owner - The owner of the property that changed.
      channel - The channel on which the change occurred.
      newValue - The new value of the property.
      oldValue - The old value of the property.

    • numberOfChangeListeners

      public long numberOfChangeListeners()
      Returns the number of change listeners that are currently registered. This is useful for debugging purposes.
      Returns:
      The number of change listeners that are currently registered.
